- content_for(:title, 'Information for Developers')
.one-column
  %h2 Requesting an Opic image
  %hr
  .row-fluid
    .span4
      %h3 Basic Request
      %p Request a user's picture using their OSU name.#:
      %p
        %code #{root_url}butsko.7
    .span4
      %h3 Width
      %p
        You can request image widths from 50 to 400 pixels in 50 pixel increments by sending a
        %code width
        parameter.
      %p
        %code #{root_url}butsko.7?width=200
    .span4
      %h3 Aspect
      %p
        By default, Opics are square. Pictures are also available in a 4:3 portrait aspect ratio. These can be requested by setting the 
        %code aspect
        parameter to p.
      %p
        %code #{root_url}butsko.7?aspect=p
      %p This works in combination with the width parameter:
      %p
        %code #{root_url}butsko.7?aspect=p&width=350

      %h2 Make Opic better
      %hr
      %p What? You think this can be better? Of course you do. Please feel free to contribute at %link_to{'our GitHub project', 'https://github.com/ASCTech/opic'}.
